==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Institutive
<hw>In"sti*tu`tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Tending or intended to institute; having the power to
establish.</def> <rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Established; depending on, or characterized by,
institution or order.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Institutive</xex>
decency.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Institutively</ent>⟦br⟧
